<h1 style="margin-bottom: 40px;">About</h1>

<h3>Why?</h3>

<p>
<big>
Many people don't know who they can vote for to represent them in parliament before seeing the ballot paper. And much of the information they have about their candidates comes from marketing, giving an advantage candidates who can pay for it. YourCandidates.org.uk aims to change this with the power of open data, by providing a neutral source of information about candidates and party policies that is specific to every single constituency.
</big>
</p>

<h3>How?</h3>

<p>
<big>
YourCandidates.org.uk works by making the content of open data sources easily readable and accessible. As such, we depend on the generosity of the people who work to make these databases available and to improve their quality. The data sources currenly in use are the following:
</big>
</p>


